## What breaks this plan

This plan would fail if the team underestimated burst traffic, if the compatibility endpoint became the bottleneck, or if GDPR deletion logic was incomplete. It would also degrade quickly if schema updates were not versioned and rolled out carefully.

## What stays human

The following decisions should remain human-led:

- Customer migration sequencing and communication.
- Privacy and retention policy choices.
- Rollback decisions during production incidents.
- Prioritization of which segments and personalization signals matter most.

These choices require product judgment and operational accountability rather than automation alone.
